From ac932d935ca1ef4fb730befa7575b07aa7c5bea6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: security-hardening-squad <security-squad@squad-with-aspire.local>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 19:01:45 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(SEC/APP-6): PII envelope encryption library + 14 tests
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Implements squads/security-hardening/artifacts/app-6-pii-encryption-spec.md v1.0.

Library (src/TravelAssistant.Security.Pii):

- IPiiCipher + EnvelopePiiCipher: AES-256-GCM, per-tenant DEK, 1h cache.

- Envelope format: v1.{wrappedDek}.{nonce}.{ciphertextPlusTag} (base64url).

- ICmkProvider abstraction + KeyVaultCmkProvider (RSA-OAEP-256 wrap).

- DataClassAttribute (Public/Internal/Sensitive) drives EF/Cosmos converters.

- AddPiiEncryption() DI extension; KV variant + caller-supplied-CMK variant.

- PiiEnvelopeFormatException (bad envelope) vs PiiKeyUnavailableException (CMK gone / cryptographic erasure).

Tests (tests/TravelAssistant.Security.Pii.Tests) - 14 green, 0 skipped:

- Mandatory 6 from spec: round-trip, nonce-uniqueness, cross-tenant fail,

  null/empty round-trip, cryptographic erasure surfaces PiiKeyUnavailable, DEK cache reuse.

- Plus 4 envelope-format guards (malformed/version/tamper) + empty-tenant guard.

- InMemoryCmkProvider test double with DestroyTenant() for erasure simulation.

Solution: adds Security.Pii + Security.Pii.Tests projects to TravelAssistant.slnx

(and re-adds Agent.Abstractions which was on disk but missing from slnx — same fix QA shipped on qa/app-2-contracts-tests).

Branch base: feat/app-2-contracts (PR #41).

Next iteration adds 3 ProductionGuard checks (IPiiCipher in DI / CmkName resolves /

no Sensitive prop without converter) — separate patch onto security/sec-1-to-5-hardening.

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
